## Critical Guardrails

### NEVER
- Drop a database or schema
- Delete infrastructure files (CI workflows, deploy scripts, `keel`, `keel.yml`)
- Push directly to main
- Skip tests to save time
- Store secrets in code or commit .env with real credentials
- Leave TODO/FIXME/HACK in committed code
- Generate ghost implementations (functions never called or tested)
- Silence errors with bare except: or except...pass

### ALWAYS
- Run tests before AND after changes
- Update .github/context/ if architecture/API/modules change
- Verify every import resolves before committing
- Keep functions under 50 lines
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Match existing code style in the file

Full guardrails (NEVER/ALWAYS/LLM-specific + verification protocol): `.github/instructions/guardrails.md`

